ICYMI - A 27-year-old COVID-19 nurse in CA recounts her experiences to @ryangabrielson. 

Nurses are stretched thin, taking out trash, even unclogging toilets, b/c janitorial staff are scared to go in COVID wards. An intimate inside look, worth your time.
https://t.co/g98SlGVh2t

ER nurse Naomi Moya bought her own N95 mask to wear to work. Her supervisor ordered her to remove it, b/c she's not treating #COVID patients. 

At the height of the pandemic, when there's a shortage of nurses, Moya is now on unpaid leave. This is happening around the country. https://t.co/SEVv7yfSLr
